  "prompt": "Are there legal frameworks in place to combat money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are several legal frameworks designed to combat money laundering at national and international levels:\n\n1. International Frameworks:\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee on Banking Supervision guidelines\n\n2. National Legislation:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n- Suspicious Activity Reporting requirements\n\n3. Key Prevention Strategies:\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Reporting suspicious financial activities\n- Criminal penalties for money laundering\n\n4. Key Regulatory Requirements:\n- Financial institutions must implement compliance programs\n- Report large cash transactions\n- Verify customer identities\n- Maintain transaction records\n\n5. International Cooperation:\n- Information sharing between countries\n- Extradition agreements\n- Joint investigations\n- Coordinated enforcement efforts\n\nThese frameworks aim to detect, prevent, and prosecute money laundering activities across different jurisdictions.",
